                    			<li>Both domestic (NRE/NRO/FCNR) and international bank statements for the last six months.</li>
                    			<li>If you are not available in India when the application form is submitted, then a General Power of Attorney duly attested by the Indian consulate in your resident country needs to be submitted. If you will be in India then the Power of Attorney can be locally notarized.</li>
